             was indicted for <rs id="t17730908-24-off119" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17730908-24-off119" type="offenceCategory" value="miscellaneous"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17730908-24-off119" type="offenceSubcategory" value="returnFromTransportation"></interp>
               being at large in the kingdom of Great Britain before the expiration of the time for which he received sentence to be transported
            </rs>. +</p>
               <p>The copy of the record was read, by which it appeared that he was capitally convicted at the session in the Old Bailey for stealing a mare, but afterwards received his majesty's mercy in condition of transportation.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17730908-24-person370">
                  William
                   Halliburton
               <interp inst="t17730908-24-person370" type="surname" value="Halliburton"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17730908-24-person370" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17730908-24-person370" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I know the prisoner; he was capitally convicted; I know nothing of the transportation; I took him at the time he was tried for stealing the mare; I am sure he is the same person; I saw him several times besides being in Court at the time he was tried. I took him at the Old George in Oxford-road; that was the time he was first taken; Heley took him now.</p>

               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17730908-24-person371">
                  John
                   Heley
               <interp inst="t17730908-24-person371" type="surname" value="Heley"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17730908-24-person371" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17730908-24-person371" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I took him coming over Westminster Bridge in a one horse chaise; I know the prisoner; I believe he is the same man.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17730908-24-person372">
                  Henry
                   Herring
               <interp inst="t17730908-24-person372" type="surname" value="Herring"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17730908-24-person372" type="given" value="Henry"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17730908-24-person372" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I assisted Heley in taking the prisoner on Westminster Bridge.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>I own myself the person, and leave it to the mercy of the Court; I was very ill used in the country and was glad to get home again. I was pardoned before for discovering the conspiracy in Tothill-fields Bridewell.</p>
               <p>Guilty. <rs id="t17730908-24-punish120" type="punishmentDescription">
